Looking for a quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Creamy Tomato Cajun Chicken Breast in just 20 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

== Potatoes ==

Boil a full #kettle{} of water.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer).

Pour the boiling water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the potatoes.

Add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-18%minutes}.

== Chicken ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British chicken breast{260%g}(diced) to the pan and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Cook until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}. Turn occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once the chicken has browned, add the garlic and @Cajun spice mix{1} (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @tomato passata{1} and @chicken stock paste{10%g} and @sugar{1/2} for the sauce. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer.

Cook until the chicken is cooked through and the sauce has thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Creamy Sauce ==

Once the sauce has thickened and the chicken is cooked, stir through the @creme fraiche{75%g} and @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Add the @baby spinach{40%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

== Mashed Potato ==

Meanwhile, once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat.

Add a knob of @butter{} and a splash of @?milk{} and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

When everything is ready, spoon the creamy tomato Cajun chicken into your bowls.

Serve the mash on the side. Enjoy!